tegies. Agent at Work | AI Docs It Be Your Own Kids - Visual Brand Identity & UGC Content Strategy View Using Tool | Doc Generate Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a comprehensive visual brand guide document for \"It Be Your Own Kids\" clothing brand with the following structure: # IT BE YOUR OWN KIDS - VISUAL BRAND GUIDE ## Strategic Foundation & Market Positioning Start with an executive summary explaining: - Brand philosophy: Acknowledging the beautiful chaos of parenting/caregiving - Core message: \"You're not alone in this crazy journey\" - Primary tone: Relatable, relaxed, humorous, with practical solutions - Target demographics broken into segments ## OPTION 1: \"REAL LIFE UNFILTERED\" Complete brand identity featuring: - Visual Style: Raw, authentic UGC aesthetic with natural lighting - Color Palette: Warm neutrals, coffee browns, soft grays (hex codes) - Typography: Sans-serif, relatable, slightly imperfect - Content Strategy: Scrapped social media rants/vents with overlaid text - Video Style: Arc Ads optimized - handheld phone footage aesthetic - Target Segments: All parent stages, focus on authenticity - Sample Mockups description - AI Generation Prompts for Sora/Veo 3 ## OPTION 2: \"COMEDY CLUB CHIC\" Complete brand identity featuring: - Visual Style: Polished UGC with comedic timing and delivery - Color Palette: Bold accent colors (wine red, coffee black, \"timeout\" blue) - Typography: Mix of hand-written style headers with clean body text - Content Strategy: Stand-up comedy style storytelling from scraped posts - Video Style: Veo 3 optimized - talking-head confessionals with quick cuts - Target Segments: Teachers, exhausted parents, grandparents - Sample Mockups description - AI Generation Prompts for Sora/Veo 3 ## OPTION 3: \"TRIBE MEMBERSHIP\" Complete brand identity featuring: - Visual Style: Community-driven, user-generated celebration - Color Palette: Inclusive earth tones with energetic pops - Typography: Modern, welcoming, slightly playful - Content Strategy: Compilation format showing \"you're not alone\" moments - Video Style: Multi-generational, showing different kid stages - Target Segments: Age-segmented (newborn→grown kids, grandparents, teachers) - Sample Mockups description - AI Generation Prompts for Sora/Veo 3 ## OPTION 4: \"SOLUTION-FORWARD SURVIVORS\" Complete brand identity featuring: - Visual Style: Before/after transformation storytelling - Color Palette: Calming colors with \"survival mode\" accents - Typography: Clear, reassuring, with handwritten \"survivor notes\" - Content Strategy: Problem acknowledgment → humor → practical tip - Video Style: Short-form tutorial style with comedic relief - Target Segments: Solution-seekers across all stages - Sample Mockups description - AI Generation Prompts for Sora/Veo 3 ## CONTENT SEGMENTATION STRATEGY Create detailed tables for: ### Age Stage Segmentation Table with columns: Stage | Age Range | Pain Points | Viral Triggers | Product Fit | Content Themes Include rows for: - Newborn/Infant (0-1) - Toddler Terror (1-3) - Preschool Chaos (3-5) - Elementary Energy (6-11) - Middle School Madness (12-14) - High School Drama (15-18) - College/Young Adult (18-25) - Grown But Not Gone (25+) - Grandparent Layer (All Ages) - Teachers by Grade Level ### Social Media Scraping Framework Table with columns: Platform | Post Type | Engagement Threshold | Viral Indicators | Scraping Tool | Content Rights Strategy ## AI VIDEO GENERATION SYSTEM ### Arc Ads Optimization - Technical specs for hyperrealistic UGC - Prompt engineering templates - Batch generation workflow - Cost optimization strategies ### Sora Integration - Scene composition guidelines - Aspect ratios for different platforms - Duration recommendations - Prompt templates by audience segment ### Veo 3 Implementation - Hyperrealistic human generation prompts - Emotion and expression guidelines - Background environment specs - Voice-over integration ### Content Production Pipeline Create flowchart descriptions for: 1. Social media scraping → sentiment analysis → content validation 2. Viral post identification → script adaptation → AI video generation 3. Segment targeting → personalization → distribution 4. Performance tracking → iteration → optimization ## BRAND IDENTITY OWNERSHIP ### Visual Assets System - Logo variations and usage - Tagline positioning: \"It Be Your Own Kids\" ownership strategy - Merchandise mockup guidelines for each product: * Wine glasses (with measurement markers) * Hoodies (design placement zones) * Baseball caps (embroidery vs print) * Blankets (pattern/text integration) ### Messaging Framework by Segment Detailed messaging for each target: - New moms: \"You're doing amazing, even when they won't sleep\" - Veteran parents: \"Survived toddlerhood, now navigating teenagehood\" - Grandparents: \"Thought I was done, but here we go again\" - Teachers: \"I teach your kids, I need wine too\" ## VIRAL CONTENT TEMPLATES ### Template Library 15+ proven formats based on scraped high-performing posts: 1. \"Things I said I'd never do as a parent\" (confession format) 2. \"My kid just...\" (shock value humor) 3. \"Teacher confessions\" (classroom chaos) 4. \"Grandparent survival guide\" (generational humor) 5. \"Stages of bedtime\" (relatable progression) [Continue with 10 more...] ### UGC Recreation Guidelines - How to identify high-viral-potential posts - Script adaptation while maintaining authenticity - Legal considerations and attribution - Talent direction for AI video generation ## IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP ### Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-2) Detailed SOP table with columns: Task | Owner | Tools | Input | Output | Success Metrics | Timeline ### Phase 2: Content Production (Weeks 3-6) - Social media scraping sprint - AI video batch generation - Asset library building - Segment testing ### Phase 3: Launch & Optimization (Weeks 7-12) - Staged rollout by segment - Performance tracking dashboard - A/B testing framework - Iteration protocols ## AI TOOLS & TECHNOLOGY STACK ### Primary Tools Detailed breakdown with: - Arc Ads: Use case, pricing, output specs, integration - Sora: Use case, pricing, output specs, integration - Veo 3: Use case, pricing, output specs, integration - Runway Gen 4: Supplementary use cases - MiniMax Hailuo 2.3: Cost-effective alternative ### Supporting Tools - Social media scraping: Apify, Octoparse, PhantomBuster - Analytics: Viral post detection algorithms - Content management: Asset organization system - Distribution: Multi-platform scheduling ## LEGAL & ETHICAL FRAMEWORK - User-generated content rights - Social media scraping compliance - Attribution strategies - Privacy considerations - Community guidelines ## MEASUREMENT & OPTIMIZATION ### KPI Dashboard by Segment Table format tracking: - Engagement rates by child age stage - Viral coefficient by content type - Conversion rates by product category - Audience growth by demographic - Cost per acquisition by channel ### Optimization Protocols - Weekly performance review checklist - Monthly strategy adjustment framework - Quarterly brand evolution assessment ## APPENDIX: QUICK REFERENCE ### Brand Voice Do's and Don'ts Side-by-side comparison tables ### Visual Style Examples Descriptions of 20+ reference images for AI generation ### Prompt Library 100+ tested prompts for Sora/Veo 3/Arc Ads organized by: - Emotion/tone - Demographic segment - Product category - Content format - Platform optimization Use professional brand guide formatting with clear hierarchy, lots of tables, callout boxes for pro tips, warning boxes for common mistakes, and framework boxes for systems. Include placeholder notes for where infographics, flowcharts, and visual mockups should be inserted. Make this a complete, implementable brand guide that a non-technical person can follow step-by-step to build a viral clothing brand using AI tools and scraped social content. Excellent! I've created a comprehensive Visual Brand Guide for \"It Be Your Own Kids\" th